name: Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod
intro:
12 Friends. 2 Vans. 200-ish Miles. Overnight. Running Relay. From Hull to Provincetown, MA. 

NEW for 2017: Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod is Going into a Lottery: 

From September 28th- October 26th, Ragnarians can enter the lottery for a chance to get into the 2017 Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod race.

  • To enter, Team Captains can pay a $25 refundable application fee plus a 5.75% service fee.  If you don’t get in, your money will be refunded — yes, even the service fee.
  • Lottery will be open from Sept. 28th - Oct. 26th. 
  • Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod participants do not have to fullfill a volunteer requirement. 
  • Find out more about the Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod lottery! 

About Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod:

Home of iconic white sand beaches, dunes and breathtaking coastal views. Reebok Ragnar Relay Cape Cod will put wind in your sails as you conquer 200ish miles from Hull to Provincetown, MA with your team. The peaceful Cape Cod scenery lives up to its famous reputation on the Ragnar course. Run on salt-weathered bridges, next to sand dunes and pasty white picket-fenced beach houses in the charming Hyannis Port. Take in the sights and some history too! Wave to tourists taking photos in front of Plymouth Rock and the Mayflower as you run by. The ocean breeze combined with cheers coming from your team van will lift your spirits and pull you towards the finish line. The 200-ish mile running party will continue under the Ragnar arch, as you share unforgettable stories and bask in the glory of what you have just accomplished. 

Interested in skipping the lottery, click here to learn how to run for our partnered charity and gain guaranteed entry.

GREAT NEWS! All 2017 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be receiving a free pair of Reebok running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!

Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod is part of the Double Medal Series. Run Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod and any other Northeast Ragnar Relay or Ragnar Trail to receive the new Northeast Double Medal - design coming soon!

We are thrilled that The Hole in the Wall Gang Camp is joining us for the 3rd year as the signature charity of Ragnar Relay Cape Cod 2017!

Founded in 1988 by Paul Newman, The Hole in the Wall Gang Camp provides "a different kind of healing" to more than 25,000 seriously ill children and family members annually - all completely free of charge. For many of these children and families, Hole in the Wall provides multiple Camp experiences throughout the year at the facility in Ashford, Conn., in more than 35 hospitals and clinics, directly in camper homes and communities, and through other outreach activities across the Northeast.

With 35% of campers coming from Eastern Massachusetts & Cape Cod, it’s a community that celebrates the fun, friendship and spirit of childhood, where every kid can “raise a little hell.” The Ragnar experience embodies what Camp is all about – camaraderie, challenge, and a healthy dose of crazy, good fun!

If you ran in 2016, chances are you saw their 246+ runners, received one of their awesome “buff” headbands and enjoyed their photo-booth at Exchange 30. Their teams raised more than $150,000 during the event, all to support seriously ill children and their families in Massachusetts.  

Through our partnership, The Hole in the Wall Gang Camp is offering the opportunity to receive FREE ENTRY to Ragnar Relay Cape Cod. Add meaning to your run and help provide “a different kind of healing” to seriously ill children and their families. Learn more on how to join The Hole in the Wall Gang Camp and help make stories like this one possible. Run Ragnar for Camp!


Dylan’s Wings of Change is a foundation established to honor the memory of Dylan Hockley who was killed in the mass shooting at Sandy Hook Elementary School on December 14th 2012. Dylan was six years old and had autism. The foundation has developed a unique youth leadership program called Wingman that creates empathy and acceptance leading to inclusion for all children. Participants explore the qualities of a Wingman such as courage, perseverance and resilience. They are recognized for their positive acts that extend far beyond respect and kindness. Wingman is active in seven middle schools in Connecticut and ready expand across New England in 2017. The most recent iteration of the program, Wingman for Dance, has been adopted by 20 studios in a dozen states. Dylan’s Wings of Change has entered teams in Ragnar Relay Cape Cod every year since 2013. Unmissable in their purple “Running for Dylan” shirts, these runners have raised over $200,000 toward the foundation’s programs and created incredible memories in the process.

Both Ragnar and wingman instill the desire to go above and beyond for others, shifting perceptions of ourselves and those around us and we re-learn how to believe. Vulnerabilities are explored and embraced; we find our significance again. The training and dedication to a common cause fosters amazing connection.  Through our partnership with Ragnar we are excited to offer free entry to Ragnar Relay Cape Cod for teams willing to fundraise and support the growth of this unique grassroots program that is transforming children’s lives. Our captains coordinate their planning efforts, developing intense camaraderie among all the teams and ensuring everyone experiences Ragnar to the fullest. Join us today! Please contact Ian Hockley: ian.hockley@dylanswingsofchange.com.

 

Ben’s Lighthouse began as a grassroots organization following the tragedy at Sandy Hook Elementary School. Founded to honor 6-year old Benjamin Wheeler, Ben’s enthusiasm for life - and his love of lighthouses - is the energy that is carried on through the work of the organization. Our mission drives us to foster all children’s potential to build a more compassionate and connected world.  Ben’s Lighthouse provides programs and opportunities that help kids and teens develop empathy, self-awareness and social connection.  The lighthouses that Ben loved provide the perfect metaphor that guides our work. From local mentoring programs to national outreach service trips, participants are encouraged to find and share their own light – to stand tall and shine bright! Last year Ben’s Lighthouse participated in Ragnar Relay Cape Cod and with four teams, raised over $48,000.00. Contact Francine Wheeler at (203) 491-2848 for more information!


REACH Newtown is a non-profit organization whose mission is to Connect Kids and Build Relationships That Change Lives!  We believe that consistency, a high number of weekly contact hours, and building trusting relationships with our kids are the key components to the incredible impact being made. We regularly observe and measure the positive impact and changes taking place in the lives of our students. REACH connects with our highest at-risk population four days during the school week, one day each weekend for outdoor expeditions, and for six full weeks throughout the summer. In addition to building and sustaining consistent, supportive relationships, which is foundational to our work, we ensure that each child is exposed to the fine arts, literacy, STEM and math enrichment, athletics, and outdoor expeditions via each of our five core programs. Every program is offered completely free of charge to every child we serve! Ragnar has always been a place for the community to show support for REACH Newtown and have a blast doing it! This will be our 4th consecutive year running for TEAM REACH in Ragnar Cape Cod!  We are proud to have over 100 runners “Running the Cape for the Kids”. Learn more on how to join TEAM REACH and help us build relationships that change lives! www.reachnewtown.org. REACH Newtown contact: Lindsey Carley: Lcarley@reachnewtown.org or 203-610-5607.

SMILE Mass is a non-profit dedicated to helping families create happy, healthy memories through vacation and recreation experiences.  Perhaps you have seen one of the AMAZING FLOATING BEACH WHEELCHAIRS (over 100) that they have donated to public beaches in Massachusetts.  Or perhaps you noticed them strapped to the top of their Ragnar vans over the last 3 years!  SMILE Mass believes that everyone deserves a day at the beach! SMILE Mass will have teams running in the Ragnar Relay Cape Cod for the 4th consecutive year!  They have raised $80,000 over the last 3 years JUST from running Ragnar.  The motto of their running team is "we run for those who can't"!  You might have seen them pushing King Nicholas across the finish line in 2014 or 2015 in his Hoyt running chair. How would you like to make a difference in the lives of families raising children or adults with disabilities?  JOIN THE SMILE MASS RUNNING TEAM. Learn more about SMILE Mass at www.smilemass.org.  To join their team, email info@smilemass.org or call Lotte at 617-967-7755!

reg_system.name: LOTTERY - Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod
reg_system.description: Home of iconic white sand beaches, dunes and breathtaking coastal views. Reebok Ragnar Relay Cape Cod will put wind in your sails as you conquer 200ish miles from Hull to Provincetown, MA with your team. The peaceful Cape Cod scenery lives up to its famous reputation on the Ragnar course. Run on salt-weathered bridges, next to sand dunes and pasty white picket-fenced beach houses in the charming Hyannis Port. Take in the sights and some history too! Wave to tourists taking photos in front of Plymouth Rock and theMayflower as you run by. The ocean breeze combined with cheers coming from your team van will lift your spirits and pull you towards the finish line. The 200 mile running party will continue under the Ragnar arch, as you share unforgettable stories and bask in the glory of what you have just accomplished.Not feeling lucky?  Lost that special rabbit's foot?  Want to skip the Lottery and run for a charity?  Visit the Reebok Ragnar Cape Cod Extra Mile page to learn more about some amazing charities you can pledge to fundraise for and skip the lottery.Reebok Ragnar Cape Code Extra Mile Program...CLICK HERE! *No volunteer requirement.
